 Network Diagnostics & Troubleshooting (Windows 11)

Objective
To demonstrate proficiency in using the Windows Command Line to diagnose and resolve common connectivity issues.

Tools & Commands Used
ipconfig /all:To verify IP, Subnet Mask, and DNS settings.
ping: To test ICMP connectivity and DNS resolution.
ipconfig /renew: To troubleshoot DHCP addressing issues.

### 3. Procedure
1. Verification: Confirmed the local IP address and gateway configuration.
   Networking troubleshooting/Screenshot (14).png
   
2. Connectivity Test: Successfully pinged external DNS (8.8.8.8) to verify internet access.
  

3. **Resolution:** Simulated a network drop and used the renew command to successfully pull a new lease from the DHCP server.
  

### 4. Outcome
Successfully identified a simulated connectivity failure and restored network access using standard CLI tools.
